  <num>5-1501.02</num>
  <heading>Establishment of the Forensic Sciences and Public Health Laboratory.</heading>
  <para placeholder="Repealed">
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>Repealed.</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(a-1)</num>
    <text>There is established as an independent agency within the executive branch of the government of the District of Columbia, the Forensic Sciences and Public Health Laboratory.</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(b)</num>
    <text>The mission of the Laboratory shall be to provide independent, high-quality, timely, accurate, and reliable forensic science services and public health laboratory services with:</text>
    <para>
      <num>(1)</num>
      <text>The use of best practices and best available technology;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(2)</num>
      <text>A focus on the delivery of unbiased science and an emphasis on promoting transparency in operations;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(2A)</num>
      <text>A commitment to timely response and accountability to customers and stakeholders; and</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(3)</num>
      <text>The goal of enhancing public health and the fair and balanced administration of justice.</text>
    </para>
  </para>
